State Security Minister Ayanda Dlodlo has given a detailed response to the allegations raised by Inspector-General of Intelligence Sethlomamaru Dintwe. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A very public spat within the State Security Agency is playing out right here on eNCA. On Wednesday Inspector-General of Intelligence Sethlomamaru Dintwe was on air and accused various ministers within the State Security Sector of political interference. He pointed fingers at State Security Minister Ayanda Dlodlo, her Police Department colleague Bheki Cele and Defence Minister, Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula. READ: Dintwe alleges interference by ministers Dintwe accuses the three of attempting to micro-manage him. Dlodlo is not taking the allegations lying down. She's given a detailed response to the allegations raised by Dintwe while he was on air on Wednesday and while he testified at the state capture inquiry.